<br>
I normally dont rant but this might be a better way than to argue with a player and regret it afterwards.<br>
<br>
Well,what happened.Got a guild tell,that we are raiding KC.Okies,the mage Lumyen is on his way to help.With over 20 players it was supposed to be an overkill but i was glad to help a guildie.Some non guildies came along too and fun began.<br>
<br>
We went in,killed the mob i have killed 100 times before and everyone was happy.<br>
<br>
Looting began and a i saw the Shissar Staff being looted.Its a mage only staff i wanted to have for a long time now. So i sent a tell to the looter if i might have the staff,as i am the only mage in the raid and its mage only. I was ignored. Okies,can happen,many people are on a raid,many tells in the window. I ask again if i may get the staff,as i am the only mage on the raid. No reply. They begin rolling for the staff. I say in raid talk if i may get the staff please.<br>
<br>
One person says,as there are no mages here,we roll for the staff.My reply is,if i am talking to walls and I am a mage. So most people begin to shout: We have a mage,give him the staff.<br>
<br>
4 polite and ignored questions later,if i might have the Shissar staff,the looter not willing to hand it to me,i give up and gate out.<br>
<br>
2 minutes later i get the tell from the looter,that he hasnt seen a mage in the raidwindow (I was there as clear as a bright day) and that he wanted to hand me the staff out.<br>
<br>
Sure,I might be dumb but not as dumb.If we argue about 7 minutes about the staff and half of the people shouting that there is a mage no one can tell me he hasnt seen it.<br>
<br>
Well,there is nothing i can do,but it felt unfair.<br>
<br>
Thanks for listening to it,feels better already to write about this topic,<br>
<br>
Lumyen Syndarin,Mageketeer of the 57th season<br>
